cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with image processing using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on demosaicking and denoising, which are subtopics of image processing and could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or graphics (cs.GR). The use of neural networks also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) could be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with processing of RAW images, which could fall under image retrieval (cs.IR).
